import Heights.ForMathlib
import Mathlib

/-!
# The ring of `S`-integers is a Dedekind domain

Let `R` be a Dedekind domain with fraction field `K` and let `S` be a set of primes of `R`.
`Mathlib.RingTheory.DedekindDomain.SInteger` defines the subalgebra `Set.integer S K` of
`S`-integers, `ūĚí™_S = {x : K | ‚ąÄ v ‚ąČ S, v x ‚Č§ 1} = ‚čā_{v ‚ąČ S} R_v`, but proves nothing about its
ring structure. This file develops it. The goal is:

* `ūĚí™_S` is a Dedekind domain with fraction field `K`;
* its height one primes are exactly the `v ‚ąČ S`, via `v ‚Ü¶ ūĚí™_S ‚ą© v`;
* its class group is `Cl(R)` modulo the subgroup generated by the classes of the `v ‚ąą S`.

These are the facts needed in `Heights.SelmerGroup` to construct the right-hand map of the
fundamental exact sequence, and they reduce the whole exact sequence to the case `S = ‚ąÖ`, where
the map to the class group is simply `x ‚Ü¶ [ūĚĒě]` for the ideal with `ūĚĒě ^ n = (x)`. They are of
independent interest, and Mathlib has none of them.

## A warning

`ūĚí™_S` is **not** in general a localization of `R`. Localizing at
`M = {r : R | r ‚Č† 0 ‚ąß ‚ąÄ v ‚ąČ S, v r = 1}` gives a subring of `ūĚí™_S`, but it can be strictly
smaller: if `Cl(R) ‚ČÖ ‚Ą§` is generated by the class of a single prime `v` and `S = {v}`, then
`M = Rň£`, because no power `v ^ k` with `k ‚Č† 0` is principal; yet `ūĚí™_S ‚äč R`, since for any
integral ideal `ūĚĒě` in the class of `v` the fractional ideal `ūĚĒě * v‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` is principal, generated by
some `x` with `v x < 1` and `w x ‚Č§ 1` for `w ‚Č† v`. So `ūĚí™_S` has to be handled as a general
overring of `R`, not as a ring of fractions.

The classical statement in the appropriate generality is that *every* overring of a Dedekind
domain (i.e. every ring between `R` and `K`) is a Dedekind domain. The proofs below use the
`S`-integer description directly (via the denominator-ideal argument in `map_comap_eq`), which
keeps them short; upstreaming to Mathlib might instead aim for the general overring statement.

## Implementation notes

`Set.integer S K` is a `Subalgebra R K`. Since it sits between `R` and `K`, the instance
`Localization.subalgebra.instIsFractionRingSubtypeMemSubalgebra` already makes `K` its fraction
field, so `HeightOneSpectrum`-style valuation theory applies as soon as we know it is a Dedekind
domain.

## Main statements

* `IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.isIntegrallyClosed`: `ūĚí™_S` is integrally closed.
* `IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.isDedekindDomain`: `ūĚí™_S` is a Dedekind domain.
* `IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.heightOneSpectrumEquiv`: the primes of `ūĚí™_S` are the `v ‚ąČ S`, and
  `valuation_heightOneSpectrumEquiv`: the valuations restrict those of `R`.
* `IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.extendedHom_surjective` and `finite_classGroup`: extension of ideals
  `Cl(R) ‚Üí Cl(ūĚí™_S)` is surjective, so `Cl(ūĚí™_S)` is finite whenever `Cl(R)` is.
* `IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.classGroupEquiv`: `Cl(ūĚí™_S) ‚ČÉ* Cl(R) ‚ßł ‚ü®[v] : v ‚ąą S‚ü©` (this one
  modulo the remaining `sorry` in `ker_extendedHom`).

## TODO

The ring `ūĚí™_S` is now known to be a Dedekind domain (`isDedekindDomain`) with height one
spectrum `{v ‚ąČ S}` (`heightOneSpectrumEquiv`), and its valuations are the restrictions of those
of `R` (`valuation_heightOneSpectrumEquiv`).  What remains is the class group:

* `ker_extendedHom` (and with it `classGroupEquiv`): the kernel of `Ideal.map` on class groups
  is the subgroup generated by the classes of the `v ‚ąą S`.

-/

open IsDedekindDomain

open scoped nonZeroDivisors

section DenomIdeal

variable {R : Type*} [CommRing R] (K : Type*) [CommRing K] [Algebra R K]

/-- The denominator ideal of `x : K`: the `r : R` with `r * x ‚ąą R`. -/
def IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.denomIdeal (x : K) : Ideal R where
  carrier := {r : R | ‚ąÉ s : R, algebraMap R K r * x = algebraMap R K s}
  zero_mem' := ‚ü®0, by simp‚ü©
  add_mem' := by
    rintro a b ‚ü®s, hs‚ü© ‚ü®t, ht‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®s + t, by rw [map_add, add_mul, hs, ht, map_add]‚ü©
  smul_mem' := by
    rintro c a ‚ü®s, hs‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®c * s, by rw [smul_eq_mul, map_mul, mul_assoc, hs, map_mul]‚ü©

lemma IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.mem_denomIdeal_iff {x : K} {r : R} :
    r ‚ąą denomIdeal K x ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÉ s : R, algebraMap R K r * x = algebraMap R K s :=
  Iff.rfl

/-- The denominator ideal is the colon ideal `(R : x)`. -/
lemma IsDedekindDomain.SInteger.denomIdeal_eq_colon (x : K) :
    denomIdeal K x = (1 : Submodule R K).colon {x} := by
  ext r
  rw [mem_denomIdeal_iff, Submodule.mem_colon_singleton, Algebra.smul_def, Submodule.mem_one]
  exact exists_congr fun s ‚Ü¶ eq_comm

end DenomIdeal

namespace IsDedekindDomain.SInteger

variable {R : Type*} [CommRing R] [IsDedekindDomain R] (K : Type*) [Field K] [Algebra R K]
  [IsFractionRing R K] (S : Set (HeightOneSpectrum R))

/-- Membership in the ring of `S`-integers is by definition integrality at all primes off `S`. -/
lemma mem_integer_iff {x : K} : x ‚ąą S.integer K ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÄ v ‚ąČ S, v.valuation K x ‚Č§ 1 := Iff.rfl

/-- The ring of `S`-integers is contained in the valuation subring of every prime off `S`. -/
lemma toSubring_le_valuationSubring {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    (S.integer K).toSubring ‚Č§ (v.valuation K).valuationSubring.toSubring :=
  fun _ hx ‚Ü¶ hx v hv

/-- The fraction field of the ring of `S`-integers is `K`. This is already an instance, as
`Set.integer S K` is a subalgebra of `K` over `R`. -/
example : IsFractionRing (S.integer K) K := inferInstance

/-- The ring of `S`-integers is integrally closed: it is an intersection of valuation subrings
of `K`, each of which is integrally closed in `K`. -/
instance isIntegrallyClosed : IsIntegrallyClosed (S.integer K) := by
  rw [isIntegrallyClosed_iff K]
  intro x hx
  refine ‚ü®‚ü®x, fun v hv ‚Ü¶ ?_‚ü©, rfl‚ü©
  -- work inside the valuation subring `V` of `v`, which contains `ūĚí™_S`
  set V := (v.valuation K).valuationSubring with hV
  let _ : Algebra (S.integer K) V :=
    (Subring.inclusion (toSubring_le_valuationSubring K S hv)).toAlgebra
  have _ : IsScalarTower (S.integer K) V K := .of_algebraMap_eq fun _ ‚Ü¶ rfl
  obtain ‚ü®y, hy‚ü© := (isIntegrallyClosed_iff K).mp inferInstance (hx.tower_top (A := V))
  rw [‚Üź hy]
  exact y.property

/-!
### Primes in `S` become the unit ideal

For `v ‚ąą S` the inverse `v‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` of `v` as a fractional ideal consists of `S`-integers, because an
element `y` with `y * v ‚äÜ R` can have a pole only at `v`. As `v * v‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = 1`, the extension of `v`
to `ūĚí™_S` is therefore the unit ideal. This is the one place where the Dedekind property of `R`
enters, and it is what makes `ūĚí™_S` bigger than `R`.
-/

/-- A height one prime is not contained in any other one. -/
lemma exists_mem_notMem {v w : HeightOneSpectrum R} (h : w ‚Č† v) :
    ‚ąÉ a ‚ąą v.asIdeal, a ‚ąČ w.asIdeal := by
  by_contra! hc
  exact h (HeightOneSpectrum.ext (v.isMaximal.eq_of_le w.isPrime.ne_top hc).symm)

/-- For `v ‚ąą S`, the fractional ideal `v‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` consists of `S`-integers. -/
lemma mem_integer_of_mem_inv {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąą S) {y : K}
    (hy : y ‚ąą (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) : y ‚ąą S.integer K := by
  intro w hw
  obtain ‚ü®a, ha, haw‚ü© := exists_mem_notMem (show w ‚Č† v by rintro rfl; exact hw hv)
  have h1 : y * algebraMap R K a ‚ąą (1 : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K) :=
    (FractionalIdeal.mem_inv_iff (FractionalIdeal.coeIdeal_ne_zero.mpr v.ne_bot)).mp hy _
      (FractionalIdeal.mem_coeIdeal_of_mem R‚Āį ha)
  obtain ‚ü®r, hr‚ü© := (FractionalIdeal.mem_one_iff _).mp h1
  have h2 : w.valuation K (y * algebraMap R K a) ‚Č§ 1 := hr ‚Ėł w.valuation_le_one r
  rwa [map_mul, w.valuation_eq_one_iff_notMem.mpr haw, mul_one] at h2

/-- For `v ‚ąą S`, the extension of `v` to the ring of `S`-integers is the unit ideal. -/
lemma map_asIdeal_eq_top {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąą S) :
    Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal = ‚ä§ := by
  set A := S.integer K with hA
  set M := Ideal.map (algebraMap R A) v.asIdeal with hM
  -- `1 ‚ąą v * v‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`, as a submodule of `K`
  have h1 : (1 : K) ‚ąą
      (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K) * (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ := by
    rw [FractionalIdeal.coe_ideal_mul_inv _ v.ne_bot]
    exact (FractionalIdeal.mem_one_iff _).mpr ‚ü®1, map_one _‚ü©
  rw [‚Üź FractionalIdeal.mem_coe, FractionalIdeal.coe_mul] at h1
  -- every element of the product that is an `S`-integer lies in `M`
  refine Ideal.eq_top_iff_one M |>.mpr ?_
  suffices H : ‚ąÄ x ‚ąą (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K) * (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ,
      ‚ąÉ hx : x ‚ąą A, (‚ü®x, hx‚ü© : A) ‚ąą M by
    obtain ‚ü®hx, hx'‚ü© := H 1 (by rwa [‚Üź FractionalIdeal.coe_mul, FractionalIdeal.mem_coe] at h1)
    exact (show (‚ü®1, hx‚ü© : A) = 1 from rfl) ‚Ėł hx'
  intro x hx
  rw [‚Üź FractionalIdeal.mem_coe, FractionalIdeal.coe_mul] at hx
  refine Submodule.mul_induction_on hx (fun a ha y hy ‚Ü¶ ?_) (fun x y hx hy ‚Ü¶ ?_)
  ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®a, ha', rfl‚ü© := (FractionalIdeal.mem_coeIdeal R‚Āį).mp
      ((FractionalIdeal.mem_coe (I := (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K))).mpr ha)
    have hyA : y ‚ąą A := mem_integer_of_mem_inv K S hv
      ((FractionalIdeal.mem_coe (I := (v.asIdeal : FractionalIdeal R‚Āį K)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)).mpr hy)
    have haA : algebraMap R K a ‚ąą A := A.algebraMap_mem a
    refine ‚ü®mul_mem haA hyA, ?_‚ü©
    have he : (‚ü®algebraMap R K a * y, mul_mem haA hyA‚ü© : A) = algebraMap R A a * ‚ü®y, hyA‚ü© := rfl
    rw [he]
    exact Ideal.mul_mem_right _ M (Ideal.mem_map_of_mem _ ha')
  ¬∑ obtain ‚ü®hx, hx'‚ü© := hx
    obtain ‚ü®hy, hy'‚ü© := hy
    exact ‚ü®add_mem hx hy, add_mem hx' hy'‚ü©

/-!
### Ideals of `ūĚí™_S` are extended from `R`

Let `I` be an ideal of `ūĚí™_S` and `J = I ‚ą© R` its contraction. For `x ‚ąą I` the denominator ideal
`ūĚĒ° x = {r : R | r * x ‚ąą R}` is divisible only by primes in `S`, because `x` is `w`-integral for
`w ‚ąČ S`. Hence `ūĚĒ° x * ūĚí™_S = ‚ä§` by `map_asIdeal_eq_top`, so `1 = ‚ąĎ dŠĶĘ cŠĶĘ` with `dŠĶĘ ‚ąą ūĚĒ° x` and
`cŠĶĘ ‚ąą ūĚí™_S`, and `x = ‚ąĎ (dŠĶĘ * x) * cŠĶĘ` exhibits `x` as an element of `J * ūĚí™_S`, since
`dŠĶĘ * x ‚ąą R ‚ą© I = J`.

Noetherianity is immediate from this: `J` is finitely generated as `R` is Noetherian, hence so
is its extension `I`.
-/

/-- The denominator ideal of an `S`-integer is not contained in any prime off `S`: at such a
prime `x` is integral, so it has a denominator away from the prime. -/
lemma denomIdeal_not_le {x : K} (hx : x ‚ąą S.integer K) {w : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hw : w ‚ąČ S) :
    ¬¨ denomIdeal K x ‚Č§ w.asIdeal := by
  obtain ‚ü®n, d, hnd‚ü© := HeightOneSpectrum.exists_primeCompl_mul_eq_of_integer w x (hx w hw)
  exact fun hle ‚Ü¶ d.property (hle ‚ü®n, by rw [mul_comm]; exact hnd‚ü©)

/-- The denominator ideal of any `x : K` is nonzero: a common denominator lies in it. -/
lemma denomIdeal_ne_bot (x : K) : denomIdeal K x ‚Č† (‚ä• : Ideal R) := by
  obtain ‚ü®‚ü®a, b, hb‚ü©, hab‚ü© := IsLocalization.surj R‚Āį x
  refine fun h0 ‚Ü¶ nonZeroDivisors.ne_zero hb ?_
  have : b ‚ąą denomIdeal K x := ‚ü®a, by rw [mul_comm]; exact hab‚ü©
  simpa [h0] using this

/-- The denominator ideal of an `S`-integer extends to the unit ideal of `ūĚí™_S`: all its prime
factors lie in `S`, and each of those extends to the unit ideal by `map_asIdeal_eq_top`. -/
lemma map_denomIdeal_eq_top {x : K} (hx : x ‚ąą S.integer K) :
    Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) (denomIdeal K x) = ‚ä§ := by
  by_contra h
  obtain ‚ü®M, hM, hle‚ü© := Ideal.exists_le_maximal _ h
  have hūĚĒ≠le : denomIdeal K x ‚Č§ M.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) :=
    (Ideal.le_comap_map).trans (Ideal.comap_mono hle)
  have hūĚĒ≠ne : M.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) ‚Č† ‚ä• :=
    fun h0 ‚Ü¶ denomIdeal_ne_bot K x (le_bot_iff.mp (h0 ‚Ėł hūĚĒ≠le))
  have hprime : (M.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K))).IsPrime := hM.isPrime.comap _
  have hwS : (‚ü®_, hprime, hūĚĒ≠ne‚ü© : HeightOneSpectrum R) ‚ąą S :=
    by_contra fun hwn ‚Ü¶ denomIdeal_not_le K S hx hwn hūĚĒ≠le
  have htop := map_asIdeal_eq_top K S hwS
  exact hM.ne_top (top_le_iff.mp (htop.ge.trans Ideal.map_comap_le))

/-- **Every ideal of `ūĚí™_S` is extended from `R`.** -/
theorem map_comap_eq (I : Ideal (S.integer K)) :
    Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) (I.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K))) = I := by
  refine le_antisymm Ideal.map_comap_le fun x hx ‚Ü¶ ?_
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  set J' := Ideal.map f (I.comap f) with hJ'
  have coeval (r : R) : ((f r : S.integer K) : K) = algebraMap R K r := by
    rw [IsScalarTower.algebraMap_apply R (S.integer K) K]; rfl
  -- for a denominator `d` of `x`, the product `f d * x` is extended from `R` and lies in `I`
  have key (d : R) (hd : d ‚ąą denomIdeal K (x : K)) : f d * x ‚ąą J' := by
    obtain ‚ü®s, hs‚ü© := hd
    have hfx : f d * x = f s := by
      apply Subtype.val_injective
      rw [Subalgebra.coe_mul, coeval d, coeval s, hs]
    rw [hfx]
    exact Ideal.mem_map_of_mem f (show f s ‚ąą I from hfx ‚Ėł I.mul_mem_left _ hx)
  -- the elements `r` with `r * x ‚ąą J'` form an ideal containing the extension of `denomIdeal`
  let K' : Ideal (S.integer K) :=
    { carrier := {r | r * x ‚ąą J'}
      zero_mem' := by simp
      add_mem' := fun {a b} ha hb ‚Ü¶ by simpa [add_mul] using J'.add_mem ha hb
      smul_mem' := fun c {a} ha ‚Ü¶ by
        simpa only [smul_eq_mul, Set.mem_setOf_eq, mul_assoc] using J'.mul_mem_left c ha }
  have hsub : Ideal.map f (denomIdeal K (x : K)) ‚Č§ K' := Ideal.map_le_iff_le_comap.mpr key
  have hmtop : Ideal.map f (denomIdeal K (x : K)) = ‚ä§ := map_denomIdeal_eq_top K S x.property
  have h1 : (1 : S.integer K) * x ‚ąą J' := hsub (hmtop.ge Submodule.mem_top)
  simpa using h1

/-!
### The Dedekind property
-/

instance isNoetherianRing : IsNoetherianRing (S.integer K) := by
  refine (isNoetherianRing_iff_ideal_fg _).mpr fun I ‚Ü¶ ?_
  rw [‚Üź map_comap_eq K S I]
  exact Ideal.FG.map (IsNoetherian.noetherian (R := R) (I.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K))))
    (algebraMap R (S.integer K))

/-- The contraction to `R` of a nonzero prime of `ūĚí™_S` is a nonzero prime: if it were zero, the
prime would be `map ‚ä• = ‚ä•` by `map_comap_eq`. -/
lemma comap_ne_bot {P : Ideal (S.integer K)} (hP : P ‚Č† ‚ä•) :
    P.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) ‚Č† ‚ä• := by
  intro h0
  exact hP (by rw [‚Üź map_comap_eq K S P, h0, Ideal.map_bot])

instance dimensionLEOne : Ring.DimensionLEOne (S.integer K) := by
  refine ‚ü®fun {P} hP hPp ‚Ü¶ ?_‚ü©
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  -- pass to a maximal ideal `M` above `P` and compare contractions in `R`
  obtain ‚ü®M, hM, hPM‚ü© := P.exists_le_maximal hPp.ne_top
  have hcP : P.comap f ‚Č† ‚ä• := comap_ne_bot K S hP
  have hMne : M ‚Č† ‚ä• := fun h ‚Ü¶ hP (le_bot_iff.mp (h ‚Ėł hPM))
  have hcM : M.comap f ‚Č† ‚ä• := comap_ne_bot K S hMne
  -- both contractions are maximal in `R`, and one contains the other, so they are equal
  have hcPmax : (P.comap f).IsMaximal :=
    Ring.DimensionLEOne.maximalOfPrime hcP (hPp.comap f)
  have hcMprime : (M.comap f).IsPrime := hM.isPrime.comap f
  have heq : P.comap f = M.comap f :=
    hcPmax.eq_of_le hcMprime.ne_top (Ideal.comap_mono hPM)
  -- lift the equality back through `map_comap_eq`
  rw [‚Üź map_comap_eq K S P, heq, map_comap_eq K S M]
  exact hM

instance isDedekindDomain : IsDedekindDomain (S.integer K) where

/-!
### The height one spectrum

The primes of `ūĚí™_S` are the primes `v ‚ąČ S`, via `v ‚Ü¶ ūĚí™_S ‚ą© v`. Under this correspondence the
`v`-adic valuation of `ūĚí™_S` is the restriction of the `v`-adic valuation of `R`, so the Selmer
group of `ūĚí™_S` relative to `‚ąÖ` is the Selmer group of `R` relative to `S`.
-/

/-- For `v ‚ąČ S`, the extension of `v` to `ūĚí™_S` is a proper ideal: it is contained in the proper
ideal of `S`-integers with `v`-valuation `< 1` (which does not contain `1`). -/
lemma map_asIdeal_ne_top {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal ‚Č† ‚ä§ := by
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  have coeval (r : R) : ((f r : S.integer K) : K) = algebraMap R K r := by
    rw [IsScalarTower.algebraMap_apply R (S.integer K) K]; rfl
  let ūĚĒ™ : Ideal (S.integer K) :=
    { carrier := {x | v.valuation K (x : K) < 1}
      zero_mem' := by simp
      add_mem' := fun {a b} ha hb ‚Ü¶ by
        rw [Set.mem_setOf_eq, Subalgebra.coe_add]
        exact lt_of_le_of_lt ((v.valuation K).map_add _ _) (max_lt ha hb)
      smul_mem' := fun c {a} ha ‚Ü¶ by
        have hc : v.valuation K (c : K) ‚Č§ 1 := c.property v hv
        rw [Set.mem_setOf_eq, smul_eq_mul, Subalgebra.coe_mul, map_mul]
        calc v.valuation K (c : K) * v.valuation K (a : K)
            ‚Č§ 1 * v.valuation K (a : K) := by gcongr
          _ = v.valuation K (a : K) := one_mul _
          _ < 1 := ha }
  have hle : Ideal.map f v.asIdeal ‚Č§ ūĚĒ™ :=
    Ideal.map_le_iff_le_comap.mpr fun a ha ‚Ü¶ by
      show v.valuation K ((f a : S.integer K) : K) < 1
      rw [coeval]; exact (v.valuation_lt_one_iff_mem a).mpr ha
  intro htop
  have h1 : v.valuation K ((1 : S.integer K) : K) < 1 := le_trans htop.ge hle Submodule.mem_top
  simp at h1

/-- For `v ‚ąČ S`, the contraction to `R` of the extension of `v` is `v` again. -/
lemma comap_map_asIdeal {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    (Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal).comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) =
      v.asIdeal := by
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  refine (v.isMaximal.eq_of_le ?_ Ideal.le_comap_map).symm
  rw [Ne, Ideal.comap_eq_top_iff]
  exact map_asIdeal_ne_top K S hv

/-- For `v ‚ąČ S`, the extension of `v` to `ūĚí™_S` is maximal. -/
lemma isMaximal_map_asIdeal {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    (Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal).IsMaximal := by
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  obtain ‚ü®M, hM, hle‚ü© := Ideal.exists_le_maximal _ (map_asIdeal_ne_top K S hv)
  have hcle : v.asIdeal ‚Č§ M.comap f := (comap_map_asIdeal K S hv).ge.trans (Ideal.comap_mono hle)
  have hceq : M.comap f = v.asIdeal :=
    (v.isMaximal.eq_of_le (hM.isPrime.comap f).ne_top hcle).symm
  rwa [‚Üź map_comap_eq K S M, hceq] at hM

/-- The extension of `v` to `ūĚí™_S` is a nonzero ideal: `v` is nonzero and the map is injective. -/
lemma map_asIdeal_ne_bot {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal ‚Č† ‚ä• := by
  intro h
  refine v.ne_bot ?_
  rw [‚Üź comap_map_asIdeal K S hv, h,
    Ideal.comap_bot_of_injective _ (FaithfulSMul.algebraMap_injective R (S.integer K))]

/-- The prime of `ūĚí™_S` above a prime `v ‚ąČ S` of `R`: the extension of `v`. -/
noncomputable def primeOfNotMem {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K) where
  asIdeal := Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal
  isPrime := (isMaximal_map_asIdeal K S hv).isPrime
  ne_bot := map_asIdeal_ne_bot K S hv

@[simp] lemma primeOfNotMem_asIdeal {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) :
    (primeOfNotMem K S hv).asIdeal = Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal :=
  rfl

/-- The prime of `R` below a prime `P` of `ūĚí™_S`. -/
noncomputable def primeBelow (P : HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K)) : HeightOneSpectrum R where
  asIdeal := P.asIdeal.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K))
  isPrime := P.isPrime.comap _
  ne_bot := comap_ne_bot K S P.ne_bot

@[simp] lemma primeBelow_asIdeal (P : HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K)) :
    (primeBelow K S P).asIdeal = P.asIdeal.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) :=
  rfl

lemma primeBelow_notMem (P : HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K)) : primeBelow K S P ‚ąČ S := by
  intro hv
  have h1 := map_asIdeal_eq_top K S hv
  rw [show (primeBelow K S P).asIdeal = P.asIdeal.comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) from rfl,
    map_comap_eq] at h1
  exact P.isPrime.ne_top h1

/-- The primes of `ūĚí™_S` are exactly the primes of `R` not in `S`. -/
noncomputable def heightOneSpectrumEquiv :
    {v : HeightOneSpectrum R // v ‚ąČ S} ‚ČÉ HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K) where
  toFun v := primeOfNotMem K S v.property
  invFun P := ‚ü®primeBelow K S P, primeBelow_notMem K S P‚ü©
  left_inv v := Subtype.ext <| HeightOneSpectrum.ext <| comap_map_asIdeal K S v.property
  right_inv P := HeightOneSpectrum.ext <| map_comap_eq K S P.asIdeal

@[simp] lemma heightOneSpectrumEquiv_apply (v : {v : HeightOneSpectrum R // v ‚ąČ S}) :
    heightOneSpectrumEquiv K S v = primeOfNotMem K S v.property :=
  rfl

@[simp] lemma heightOneSpectrumEquiv_symm_apply (P : HeightOneSpectrum (S.integer K)) :
    ((heightOneSpectrumEquiv K S).symm P : HeightOneSpectrum R) = primeBelow K S P :=
  rfl

/-- For `v ‚ąČ S`, the contraction of the extension of `v ^ n` is `v ^ n`: the contraction divides
`v ^ n`, so it is `v ^ j`; extending back gives `P‚Īľ = P‚āô`, whence `j = n`. -/
lemma comap_map_pow {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) (n : ‚Ąē) :
    (Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) (v.asIdeal ^ n)).comap
        (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) = v.asIdeal ^ n := by
  set f := algebraMap R (S.integer K) with hf
  have hP0 : Ideal.map f v.asIdeal ‚Č† 0 := map_asIdeal_ne_bot K S hv
  have hPnu : ¬¨ IsUnit (Ideal.map f v.asIdeal) :=
    fun h ‚Ü¶ map_asIdeal_ne_top K S hv (Ideal.isUnit_iff.mp h)
  refine le_antisymm ?_ Ideal.le_comap_map
  have hdvd : (Ideal.map f (v.asIdeal ^ n)).comap f ‚ą£ v.asIdeal ^ n :=
    Ideal.dvd_iff_le.mpr Ideal.le_comap_map
  obtain ‚ü®j, -, hassoc‚ü© := (dvd_prime_pow v.prime n).mp hdvd
  rw [associated_iff_eq] at hassoc
  have hmapQ : Ideal.map f ((Ideal.map f (v.asIdeal ^ n)).comap f) =
      Ideal.map f (v.asIdeal ^ n) := map_comap_eq K S _
  rw [hassoc, Ideal.map_pow, Ideal.map_pow] at hmapQ
  rw [hassoc, (pow_inj_of_not_isUnit hPnu hP0).mp hmapQ]

/-- For `v ‚ąČ S`, the `PŠĶ•`-adic valuation on `R` (computed in `ūĚí™_S`) is the `v`-adic valuation:
the two chains of prime powers `v ^ k` and `PŠĶ• ^ k` have matching membership. -/
lemma intValuationDef_map {v : HeightOneSpectrum R} (hv : v ‚ąČ S) (a : R) :
    (primeOfNotMem K S hv).intValuationDef (algebraMap R (S.integer K) a) =
      v.intValuationDef a := by
  rcases eq_or_ne a 0 with rfl | ha
  ¬∑ simp
  have hfa : algebraMap R (S.integer K) a ‚Č† 0 := fun h ‚Ü¶ ha
    (FaithfulSMul.algebraMap_injective R (S.integer K)
      (h.trans (map_zero (algebraMap R (S.integer K))).symm))
  have hmem (k : ‚Ąē) : a ‚ąą v.asIdeal ^ k ‚ÜĒ
      algebraMap R (S.integer K) a ‚ąą (primeOfNotMem K S hv).asIdeal ^ k := by
    rw [primeOfNotMem_asIdeal, ‚Üź Ideal.map_pow, ‚Üź Ideal.mem_comap, comap_map_pow K S hv]
  suffices h : Associates.count (Associates.mk (primeOfNotMem K S hv).asIdeal)
        (Associates.mk (Ideal.span {algebraMap R (S.integer K) a})).factors =
      Associates.count (Associates.mk v.asIdeal) (Associates.mk (Ideal.span {a})).factors by
    rw [v.intValuationDef_if_neg ha, (primeOfNotMem K S hv).intValuationDef_if_neg hfa, h]
  refine Nat.le_antisymm ?_ ?_
  ¬∑ exact (v.le_count_iff ha _).mpr
      ((hmem _).mpr (((primeOfNotMem K S hv).le_count_iff hfa _).mp le_rfl))
  ¬∑ exact ((primeOfNotMem K S hv).le_count_iff hfa _).mpr
      ((hmem _).mp ((v.le_count_iff ha _).mp le_rfl))

/-- The valuation of `ūĚí™_S` at the prime above `v` is the valuation of `R` at `v`. -/
lemma valuation_heightOneSpectrumEquiv (v : {v : HeightOneSpectrum R // v ‚ąČ S}) (x : K) :
    (heightOneSpectrumEquiv K S v).valuation K x = (v : HeightOneSpectrum R).valuation K x := by
  have hR (a : R) : (heightOneSpectrumEquiv K S v).valuation K (algebraMap R K a) =
      (v : HeightOneSpectrum R).valuation K (algebraMap R K a) := by
    have e1 : (heightOneSpectrumEquiv K S v).valuation K (algebraMap R K a) =
        (primeOfNotMem K S v.property).intValuationDef (algebraMap R (S.integer K) a) := by
      rw [IsScalarTower.algebraMap_apply R (S.integer K) K a,
        HeightOneSpectrum.valuation_of_algebraMap]; rfl
    rw [e1, intValuationDef_map K S v.property a, HeightOneSpectrum.valuation_of_algebraMap]; rfl
  obtain ‚ü®a, b, -, rfl‚ü© := IsFractionRing.div_surjective (A := R) x
  rw [map_div‚āÄ, map_div‚āÄ, hR a, hR b]

/-!
### The class group
-/

/-- `ūĚí™_S` is torsion-free over `R`, as `R` embeds into it. -/
instance : Module.IsTorsionFree R (S.integer K) := by
  rw [Module.isTorsionFree_iff_algebraMap_injective]
  exact FaithfulSMul.algebraMap_injective R (S.integer K)

/-- Extension of ideals `Cl(R) ‚Üí Cl(ūĚí™_S)` is surjective: every ideal of `ūĚí™_S` is extended from
`R` (`map_comap_eq`). -/
lemma extendedHom_surjective :
    Function.Surjective (ClassGroup.extendedHom R (S.integer K)) := by
  intro c
  obtain ‚ü®I, rfl‚ü© := ClassGroup.mk0_surjective c
  have hI : (I : Ideal (S.integer K)) ‚Č† ‚ä• := by
    have := I.2; rwa [mem_nonZeroDivisors_iff_ne_zero] at this
  refine ‚ü®ClassGroup.mk0 ‚ü®(I : Ideal (S.integer K)).comap (algebraMap R (S.integer K)),
    mem_nonZeroDivisors_iff_ne_zero.mpr (comap_ne_bot K S hI)‚ü©, ?_‚ü©
  rw [ClassGroup.extendedHom_mk0]
  exact congrArg _ (Subtype.ext (map_comap_eq K S _))

/-- The class group of `ūĚí™_S` is finite as soon as that of `R` is, being a quotient of it. -/
instance finite_classGroup [Finite (ClassGroup R)] : Finite (ClassGroup (S.integer K)) :=
  .of_surjective _ (extendedHom_surjective K S)

/-- The classes of primes in `S` lie in the kernel of extension: such primes extend to `‚ä§`. -/
lemma closure_le_ker_extendedHom :
    Subgroup.closure (HeightOneSpectrum.classGroupMk '' S) ‚Č§
      (ClassGroup.extendedHom R (S.integer K)).ker := by
  rw [Subgroup.closure_le]
  rintro _ ‚ü®v, hv, rfl‚ü©
  rw [SetLike.mem_coe, MonoidHom.mem_ker, HeightOneSpectrum.classGroupMk,
    ClassGroup.extendedHom_mk0]
  refine (ClassGroup.mk0_eq_one_iff _).mpr ?_
  show (Ideal.map (algebraMap R (S.integer K)) v.asIdeal).IsPrincipal
  rw [map_asIdeal_eq_top K S hv]
  exact ‚ü®1, by simp‚ü©

/-- The kernel of extension is generated by the classes of the primes in `S`.

The inclusion `‚äá` is `closure_le_ker_extendedHom`. For `‚äÜ`: if `map J` is principal, say
`map J = (ő≤)` with `ő≤ ‚ąą ūĚí™_S ‚äÜ K`, then for every prime `w ‚ąČ S` the `w`-adic valuations of `J`
and of `ő≤` agree (both equal the `PŠĶ•`-adic valuation of `map J`, using
`valuation_heightOneSpectrumEquiv`), so `J` and the principal fractional ideal `(ő≤)` of `R`
differ only at primes of `S`. As `(ő≤)` is principal, `[J]` lies in the subgroup generated by
the classes of the primes in `S`.

TODO: formalize `‚äÜ`. It needs the factorization `mk0 J = ‚ąŹ (classGroupMk w) ^ (ord_w J)` in
`ClassGroup R` and the equality `ord_w J = ord_w ő≤` for `w ‚ąČ S` (the ideal-level count transfer,
extending `comap_map_pow`). -/
lemma ker_extendedHom :
    (ClassGroup.extendedHom R (S.integer K)).ker =
      Subgroup.closure (HeightOneSpectrum.classGroupMk '' S) :=
  le_antisymm sorry (closure_le_ker_extendedHom K S)

/-- The class group of `ūĚí™_S` is the class group of `R` modulo the classes of the primes in `S`:
the first isomorphism theorem applied to extension of ideals. -/
noncomputable def classGroupEquiv :
    ClassGroup (S.integer K) ‚ČÉ*
      ClassGroup R ‚ßł Subgroup.closure (HeightOneSpectrum.classGroupMk '' S) :=
  (QuotientGroup.quotientKerEquivOfSurjective _ (extendedHom_surjective K S)).symm.trans
    (QuotientGroup.quotientMulEquivOfEq (ker_extendedHom K S))

end IsDedekindDomain.SInteger
